iness cases, De Langhe and Puntoni offer four pillars of decision-driven analytics and guide you around common mistakes that have held back many organizations from using data for impact.In Decision-Driven Analytics, you will learn how to:+ Avoid common pitfalls in data-driven decision-making;+ Close the gap between managers and decision-making on one side, and data scientists and data analytics on the other;+ Enhance the impact of data analytics on business outcomes;+ Think without data to make better decisions;+ Prepare for artificial intelligence’s impact on data analytics; and+ Evaluate the costs and benefits of decision-driven analytics.A must-read for anyone who wants to harness the power of data for competitive advantage, Decision-Driven Analytics will equip you with the skills and tools you need to more effectively use data for business outcomes and to make better decisions in today’s complex and data-rich world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aData mining. 0aDecision makingxData processing. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Decision-Making & Problem Solving.2bisacsh  aAI artificial intelligence.  aData driven decisions.  aHow businesses use data.  aHow to use data for business decisions.  aanalytics.  abehavioral science.  abest practices techniques.  abusiness outcomes.  acustomers.  adecision driven analytics.  askills tools.  auncertainty.1 aPuntoni, Stefano, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079136540uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/9781613631737?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781613631737423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781613631737/original  a978-3-11-079136-5  University of Pennsylvania Press Comple